terrain.desc:
“Novi, placed among vineyards at the base of the Apennine, contains six thousand inhabitants, several magnificent houses, which belong to opulent Genovesi, who spend the autumn here; and two Inns; 
                                  it is, therefore, the best sleeping place between Turin and Genoa, both on account of the last-named circumstance, and likewise from being situated about midway ”
                                  (Starke,  Travels in Europe [1833], 118).
